RDA Registry Label:
has authorized access point for work
has nomen string
has scheme of normen
Justification for Mapping: mint nomen, concatenate into nomen string all subfields omitting h (Medium, obsolete for RDA) and l (Language, which should be an expression property).  Category of nomen added from tag label since we can't identify scheme of nomen
Transformation Notes:
[this work URI] -->rdawoP10331-->[minted nomen]-->rdanP80068 " (a+d+f+g+k+m+n+o+p+r+s+ as they occur in order in MARC,separate by 1 space)"

[nomen]-->rdanP80069-->(derive from source code in $2 or domain of IRI in $0 or $1 if domain is an approved one.  If it isn't use "has access point for work" mapping)

MARCSubfieldLabel: Authority record control number or standard number (R)
Justification for Mapping: if a link to an authority record is in $0, it describes the nomen we are creating for the Work property, unless a $l (language) is present - if $l is present, it describes the nomen for the expression property.
Transformation Notes: if a link to an authority record is in $0, it describes the nomen we are creating for the Work property, unless a $l (language) is present - if $l is present, it describes the nomen for the expression property.   Just map this normen property to contents of $0

MARCSubfieldLabel: Authority record control number or standard number (R)
MARCTagCondition1: $0 contains an identifier that isn't an IRI
Justification for Mapping: If an identifier not an IRI is in $0, we can associate it with the nomen in some way and simplest way is "note on nomen"
Transformation Notes:
If an identifier not IRI is in $0, and field doesn't contain $l it describes the nomen we create for the Work property, 
[minted nomen for aap or ap of Work] -- "Authority record control number or standard number:  [contents of $0]"

If field contains $l, map this to the nomen for expression.
